{"title_page": "La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas\n| image          = La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas.jpg\n| caption        = Mexican theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Luis Mandoki]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n*[[Abraham Zabludovsky]]\n*Gerardo Barrera\n*Perla Ciuk\n}}\n| screenplay     = Diana Cardozo\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n*Greisy Mena\n*Angelina Pel\u00e1ez\n}}\n| music          = {{plainlist|\n*Alejandro Casta\u00f1os\n*Pablo Valero\n}}\n| cinematography = Dami\u00e1n Garc\u00eda\n| editing        = Mariana Rodr\u00edguez\n| production companies = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = November 9, 2012\n| runtime        = 116 minutes\n| country        = Mexico\n| language       = Spanish\n| budget         = 60,000,000 MX\n}}\n'''''La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas''''' (\"The Precocious and Brief Life of Sabina Rivas\") is a 2012 Mexican [[drama (genre)|drama]] directed by [[Luis Mandoki]]. The film received eleven nominations at the [[55th Ariel Awards]] including [[Ariel Award for Best Director|Best Director]] for Mandoki.<ref name=Ariel-SabinaRivas>{{cite news|url=http://v1.academiamexicanadecine.org.mx/ver_ariel.asp?tipo=pelicula&idPelicula=5625|title=Ariel&nbsp;\u2014 Ganadores y nominados&nbsp;\u2014La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas|year=2013|accessdate=April 5, 2017|publisher=Asociaci\u00f3n Mexicana de Artes y Ciencias Cinematogr\u00e1ficas|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nLovers as young teenagers, Sabina and Jovany, Hondurans living on the Mexican-Guatemalan border, meet after without seeing each other for some time. They are still teenagers.\n\nShe is working in a strip joint but wants to get to the United States and to be a great singer; he has become a member of la [[Mara Salvatrucha]], commiting the atrocities needed to join the gang. At the border they must deal with exploitation and harassment by migratory agents, brothel matrons, consular officials, drug traffickers, the army and la Mara Salvatrucha.\n\n==Cast==\n*{{Interlanguage link|Greisy Mena|es}} as Sabina Rivas\n*[[Joaqu\u00edn Cos\u00edo]] as Burrona\n*Fernando Moreno as Jovany\n*{{Interlanguage link|Angelina Pel\u00e1ez|es}} as Do\u00f1a Lita\n*Mario Zaragoza as Sarabia\n*Beto Benitez as A\u00f1orve\n*[[Nick Chinlund]] as Patrick\n*Miguel Flores as Don Nico\n*Arg\u00e9l Galindo as Poisson\n*[[Tenoch Huerta Mej\u00eda]] as Juan\n*Dagoberto Gama as General Valderrama\n*Luis Eduardo Yee as Pedro\n*Tito Vasconcelos as Presentador Tijuanita\n*Jos\u00e9 Sefami as Coss\u00edo\n*Asur Zagada as Thal\u00eda\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Award / Film Festival\n! scope=\"col\" |Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\" |Category\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%;\"|Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\" |Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"11\"| [[Ariel Award]]s\n| rowspan=\"11\"| [[55th Ariel Awards|2013]]\n| [[Ariel Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| {{sort|Mandoki|[[Luis Mandoki]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=Ariel-SabinaRivas/>\n|-\n| [[Ariel Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| {{sort|Mena|Greisy Mena}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Ariel Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{sort|Pelaez|Angelina Pel\u00e1ez}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Adapted Screenplay\n| {{sort|Cardozo|Diana Cardozo}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Cinematography\n| {{sort|Garcia|Dami\u00e1n Garc\u00eda}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Sound\n| {{sort|Hernandez|[[Martin Hern\u00e1ndez]]}} and Fernando C\u00e1mara\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Original Score\n| {{sort|Casta|Alejandro Casta\u00f1os}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Art Direction\n| {{sort|Muho|Antonio Mu\u00f1ohierro}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Costume Design\n| {{sort|Corta|Adela Cort\u00e1zar}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Makeup\n| {{sort|Garcia|Alfredo Garc\u00eda}} and Carla Tinoco\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Special Effects\n| {{sort|Duran|Adri\u00e1n Dur\u00e1n}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2062575|La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Luis Mandoki}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas}}\n[[Category:2012 films]]\n[[Category:2012 drama films]]\n[[Category:Mexican films]]\n[[Category:Mexican drama films]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Luis Mandoki]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas\n| image          = La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas.jpg\n| caption        = Mexican theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Luis Mandoki]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n*[[Abraham Zabludovsky]]\n*Gerardo Barrera\n*Perla Ciuk\n}}\n| screenplay     = Diana Cardozo\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n*Greisy Mena\n*Angelina Pel\u00e1ez\n}}\n| music          = {{plainlist|\n*Alejandro Casta\u00f1os\n*Pablo Valero\n}}\n| cinematography = Dami\u00e1n Garc\u00eda\n| editing        = Mariana Rodr\u00edguez\n| production companies = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = November 9, 2012\n| runtime        = 116 minutes\n| country        = Mexico\n| language       = Spanish\n| budget         = 60,000,000 MX\n}}\n'''''La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas''''' (\"The Precocious and Brief Life of Sabina Rivas\") is a 2012 Mexican [[drama (genre)|drama]] directed by [[Luis Mandoki]]. The film received eleven nominations at the [[55th Ariel Awards]] including [[Ariel Award for Best Director|Best Director]] for Mandoki.<ref name=Ariel-SabinaRivas>{{cite news|url=http://v1.academiamexicanadecine.org.mx/ver_ariel.asp?tipo=pelicula&idPelicula=5625|title=Ariel&nbsp;\u2014 Ganadores y nominados&nbsp;\u2014La vida precoz y breve de Sabina Rivas|year=2013|accessdate=April 5, 2017|publisher=Asociaci\u00f3n Mexicana de Artes y Ciencias Cinematogr\u00e1ficas|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nLovers as teenagers, Sabina and Jovany, Hondurans living on the Mexican-Guatemalan border, accidentally meet after years without seeing each other. \n\nShe wants to get to the United States and to be a great singer; he has become a member of la [[Mara Salvatrucha]], commiting the atrocities needed to join the gang. At the border they must deal with exploitation and harassment by migratory agents, brothel matrons, consular officials, drug traffickers, the army and la Mara Salvatrucha.\n\n==Cast==\n*{{Interlanguage link|Greisy Mena|es}} as Sabina Rivas\n*[[Joaqu\u00edn Cos\u00edo]] as Burrona\n*Fernando Moreno as Jovany\n*{{Interlanguage link|Angelina Pel\u00e1ez|es}} as Do\u00f1a Lita\n*Mario Zaragoza as Sarabia\n*Beto Benitez as A\u00f1orve\n*[[Nick Chinlund]] as Patrick\n*Miguel Flores as Don Nico\n*Arg\u00e9l Galindo as Poisson\n*[[Tenoch Huerta Mej\u00eda]] as Juan\n*Dagoberto Gama as General Valderrama\n*Luis Eduardo Yee as Pedro\n*Tito Vasconcelos as Presentador Tijuanita\n*Jos\u00e9 Sefami as Coss\u00edo\n*Asur Zagada as Thal\u00eda\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Award / Film Festival\n! scope=\"col\" |Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\" |Category\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"30%;\"|Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\" |Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"11\"| [[Ariel Award]]s\n| rowspan=\"11\"| [[55th Ariel Awards|2013]]\n| [[Ariel Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| {{sort|Mandoki|[[Luis Mandoki]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=Ariel-SabinaRivas/>\n|-\n| [[Ariel Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| {{sort|Mena|Greisy Mena}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Ariel Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actres